      <div class="column_paragraph" id="ca657348">
        <div class="txst-rich-text gato-rich-editor"><h2 class="h3styles">Michael Cuscuna Tribute to Dan</h2>

<p>Michael Cuscuna is an American jazz record producer and writer. He is a leading discographer of Blue Note Records. He has 3 Grammys and attributes his writing skills to working with Dan Morgenstern. In the 1960's he contributed articles to DownBeat magazine, when Dan was editor.<br>
<a href="https://docs.gato.txst.edu/199364/Paul%20Bley%20-%20Being%20Together.pdf">Read his 1st Downbeat review of Paul Bley, and edited by Dan.</a><br>
- 1992: Best Historical Album for Nat King Cole, The Complete Capitol Trio Recordings<br>
- 1998: Best Album Notes for Miles Davis, Miles Davis Quintet, 1965â€“68: The Complete Columbia Studio Recordings&nbsp;<br>
- 2001: Best Historical Album for Billie Holiday, Lady Day: The Complete Billie Holiday on Columbia.<a href="http://www.mosaicrecords.com/story.asp">Read his story how he founded Mosaic Records.</a><br>
[closed captioned] <strong><a href="https://docs.gato.txst.edu/199367/Michael%20Cuscuna%20Tribute%20to%20Dan.pdf">[transcript]</a></strong></p>

